               <p>First London Jury, before Mr. Common Sergeant.</p>
               <p>113. 
               
                  <persName id="t18311201-113-defend961" type="defendantName">
                     JOHN 
                     ROBINSON
                  <interp inst="t18311201-113-defend961" type="surname" value="ROBINSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-113-defend961" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-113-defend961" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-113-defend961" type="age" value="19"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t18311201-113-off609" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18311201-113-off609" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-113-off609" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18311201-113-cd610" type="crimeDate">21st of October</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-113-off609 t18311201-113-cd610"></join>, 1 handkerchief, value 4s., the goods of 
                     <persName id="t18311201-113-victim962" type="victimName">
                        George John 
                        Clode
                     <interp inst="t18311201-113-victim962" type="surname" value="Clode"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18311201-113-victim962" type="given" value="George John"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18311201-113-victim962" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-113-off609 t18311201-113-victim962"></join>
                     </persName>
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>GEORGE JOHN CLODE. On the 21st of October I was in Bishopsgate-street, and turned up <placeName id="t18311201-113-crimeloc611">Artillery-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18311201-113-crimeloc611" type="placeName" value="Artillery-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18311201-113-crimeloc611" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-113-off609 t18311201-113-crimeloc611"></join>; I was told my pocket was picked; I felt, and my handkerchief was gone - the prisoner was pointed out to me; I pursued, and captured him in Sun-square - I gave him in charge of an officer, who found my handkerchief on him - this is it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18311201-113-person963">
                  JOHN 
                  BOOKER
               <interp inst="t18311201-113-person963" type="surname" value="BOOKER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-113-person963" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-113-person963" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I was at the Committee-room at the workhouse, and heard the alarm; I took the prisoner in Denning's-yard, and found the handkerchief in his hat; he had been taken in Sun-square.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18311201-113-person964">
                  HANNAH 
                  LAWRENCE
               <interp inst="t18311201-113-person964" type="surname" value="LAWRENCE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-113-person964" type="given" value="HANNAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-113-person964" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw a man in the prisoner's company take the handkerchief from the prosecutor's pocket, and give it to another person, but I cannot say it was to the prisoner.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. She said she saw nothing given to me; I saw this handkerchief lay up a turning - I took it, and put it into my hat; I went on, and heard a cry of Stop thief! and the gentleman said I had got his handkerchief; I said I had one, which I found.</p>
               <p>One witness gave the prisoner a good character.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18311201-113-verdict612" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18311201-113-verdict612" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 19. - <rs id="t18311201-113-punish613" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18311201-113-punish613" type="punishmentCategory" value="imprison"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-113-defend961 t18311201-113-punish613"></join>
               Confined Six Months
            </rs>.</p>
